public class PlayerItemFrameChangeEvent extends PlayerEvent implements Cancellable
Called when an ItemFrame is having an item rotated, added, or removed from it.

    • getItemStack

      @NotNull public @NotNull ItemStack getItemStack()
      Gets the ItemStack involved in this event. This is the item being added, rotated, or removed from the ItemFrame.

      If this method returns air, then the resulting item in the ItemFrame will be empty.

      Returns:
      the ItemStack being added, rotated, or removed

    • setItemStack

      public void setItemStack(@Nullable @Nullable ItemStack itemStack)
      Sets the ItemStack that this ItemFrame holds. If null is provided, the ItemStack will become air and the result in the ItemFrame will be empty.
      Parameters:
      itemStack - ItemFrame item
